# MilePilot Golden Foundation (v8.43.67)

**Base version:** v8.43.67 · branch `cursor/restore-validated-flow-e91d`  
**Docs:** `docs/DEVELOPMENT_RULES.md`

## Non-negotiable

1. Never modify unrelated files.
2. Never perform broad refactors.
3. Never rewrite working logic for cleanliness.
4. Never change native tracking, background location, motion detection, trip completion, reports, permissions, or email delivery during UI work.
5. Never replace complete files unless explicitly authorised.
6. Never invent new copy, screens, routes, or functionality.
7. Never combine multiple objectives into one implementation.
8. Never report success without: files changed, exact behaviour changed, tests performed, protected systems untouched.
9. If protected engine code must be touched — STOP and explain why before editing.
10. Preserve a rollback point before every implementation.

## Workflow (mandatory)

Audit → Report → **Receive approval** → Implement **one** objective → Test → Screenshots → Approve → Lock → Move on.

The user-facing app must **never** be left partially functioning.

## Protected (STOP unless user explicitly requests)

- `src/nativeTrackingEngine.js`, `src/nativeAutopilot.js`, `src/nativeAutoEnd.js`, `src/locationTask.js`, `src/expoLocationBridge.js`
- Tracking block in `frontend/index.html`
- `frontend/js/autopilot-motion.js`, `frontend/js/trip-auto-end.js`, `frontend/js/summary-reports.js`
- `backend/reportEngine.js`, `backend/server.js` (email/report routes)
- `scripts/tracking-contract.json`, `scripts/home-ui-contract.json`

## Before editing

Read `docs/DEVELOPMENT_RULES.md`. State which files you will touch and which protected systems you will NOT touch. Wait for approval on non-trivial tasks.
